===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[ad]]'' '''to''' + ''[[verbum]]'' '''word'''

===[[Noun]]===

'''Adverbs''' are words which modify a [[verb]], [[adjective]], or another [[adverb]].

In the English language adverbs generally end with -ly.

Their comparative is: "more -ly"

and superlative: "most -ly"

Exceptions from these rules are:

*[[hard]]
*[[well]]


